WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:0
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:12.900 --> 00:00:14.630
Inherited will...

3
00:00:14.630 --> 00:00:17.540
the tides of time, and humanity's dreams...

4
00:00:17.540 --> 00:00:20.370
They cannot be stopped.

5
00:00:20.370 --> 00:00:23.480
As long as people seek freedom,

6
00:00:23.480 --> 00:00:26.110
these things will never cease to be.

7
00:00:34.820 --> 00:00:41.040
Mirai dake shinjiteru dareka ga warattemo kamawanai
I only believe in the future -- I don't care if anyone laughs

8
00:00:41.080 --> 00:00:46.560
Hashitteru jounetsu ga anata wo KIRA mekaseru
That racing passion makes you shine

9
00:00:46.580 --> 00:00:52.100
Mabushi sugi, demo mitsumete itai
It's too bright, but I want to gaze at it

10
00:00:52.440 --> 00:00:56.080
Dokka "bigaku" kanjiteru
I sense "aesthetics" somewhere

11
00:00:56.080 --> 00:00:58.120
I'm really really stuck on you

12
00:00:59.440 --> 00:01:02.700
Dare ni mo nitenai yume no senaka wo
I follow, follow in the footsteps

13
00:01:02.700 --> 00:01:05.990
Oikakete oikaketeku
of a dream that resembles no one

14
00:01:05.990 --> 00:01:09.220
DORAMATIKKU te ni ireru made
Until I dramatically get it

15
00:01:09.240 --> 00:01:15.040
Believe in Wonderland!

16
00:01:18.080 --> 00:01:21.120
Dare ni mo mienai yume no KATACHI wo
I'm going to catch, catch the shape

17
00:01:21.220 --> 00:01:24.200
Tsukamaete tsukamaeteku
of a dream no one can see

18
00:01:24.480 --> 00:01:30.220
Watashi wa tsuite yuku kara atsui KIMOCHI
I'm going to go with you, so passionate feelings

19
00:01:30.460 --> 00:01:33.580
TSUJITSUMA awase betsu ni iranai
I don't really need everything to add up

20
00:01:33.560 --> 00:01:36.750
Arifureta nichijou yori mo
Rather than run-of-the-mill daily life,

21
00:01:36.760 --> 00:01:40.350
PARADAISU mezashite hashire
run for paradise instead

22
00:01:40.350 --> 00:01:45.880
Believe in Wonderland!

23
00:01:52.430 --> 00:01:53.890
Princess Vivi!

24
00:01:54.420 --> 00:01:56.600
This desert will be...

25
00:01:57.030 --> 00:01:58.890
your grave!

26
00:02:00.750 --> 00:02:01.770
Un...

27
00:02:02.130 --> 00:02:03.060
Deux...

28
00:02:03.060 --> 00:02:04.630
Ourrois!

29
00:02:04.630 --> 00:02:05.730
Karoo!

30
00:02:05.790 --> 00:02:11.940
Molehill Zone Four

31
00:02:13.980 --> 00:02:15.690
Ho hum.

32
00:02:15.690 --> 00:02:19.830
Still, you're not getting away!

33
00:02:21.640 --> 00:02:23.810
Swan Dash!

34
00:02:28.870 --> 00:02:31.890
I told you, you won't get away!

35
00:02:31.890 --> 00:02:34.280
Come on, wait up, I say!

36
00:02:34.280 --> 00:02:37.990
I'm going to gobble up
the both of you!

37
00:02:42.240 --> 00:02:43.260
Karoo...

38
00:02:48.250 --> 00:02:49.790
You shielded me...

39
00:02:51.640 --> 00:02:54.190
You're in no shape
to be running anymore...

40
00:02:59.080 --> 00:03:01.870
No! If you go straight,
we'll be trapped on the stairway!

41
00:03:02.320 --> 00:03:05.830
Hold it, I'm telling you!

42
00:03:07.000 --> 00:03:10.290
Let me off, Karoo!
I'm going to fight him!

43
00:03:13.900 --> 00:03:15.470
Wait, that way is the cliff!

44
00:03:18.670 --> 00:03:20.640
Huh? That's ludicrous!

45
00:03:26.560 --> 00:03:31.020
What is this?! That duck is scaling
the sheer cliffs of Alubarna!

46
00:03:43.150 --> 00:03:43.910
You dummy!

47
00:03:43.910 --> 00:03:48.830
Now, kindly tumble back down here
and fall prey to my okama kenpo!

48
00:03:56.160 --> 00:03:57.510
What is this?!

49
00:03:58.310 --> 00:04:01.210
K-Karoo! That was amazing!
You just flew!

50
00:04:03.110 --> 00:04:05.850
Mr. 2 can't follow us
after we've come this far.

51
00:04:06.730 --> 00:04:10.680
That was sassy of you, duck!

52
00:04:10.680 --> 00:04:13.380
Nothing is impossible for me!

53
00:04:13.380 --> 00:04:16.690
Not with the relevé of my kenpo's
blood, sweat, and tears!

54
00:04:30.080 --> 00:04:33.120
Karoo, can you make it
past this battlefield?

55
00:04:33.580 --> 00:04:37.150
We can't find Koza
in all of this confusion,

56
00:04:37.150 --> 00:04:39.550
so we'll go to the palace
and find Chaka

57
00:04:39.550 --> 00:04:43.510
before the Rebel Army reaches
the heart of the city.

58
00:04:46.720 --> 00:04:50.810
I caught up to you!

59
00:05:00.380 --> 00:05:02.070
A stray bullet?!

60
00:05:02.070 --> 00:05:03.370
Karoo!

61
00:05:03.850 --> 00:05:05.970
Vivi is our friend.

62
00:05:15.040 --> 00:05:16.340
It's no use!

63
00:05:30.250 --> 00:05:31.430
Karoo...

64
00:05:35.970 --> 00:05:38.230
Karoo!

65
00:05:54.710 --> 00:05:58.170
Like I said, it's no use!

66
00:06:04.480 --> 00:06:06.050
I understand...

67
00:06:08.680 --> 00:06:13.060
You stay out of my way,
or I'll deal with you too!

68
00:06:15.330 --> 00:06:18.020
Stop!

69
00:06:32.290 --> 00:06:33.620
Y-You guys...

70
00:06:39.670 --> 00:06:43.880
Nice work, Commander Karoo.
You're the man.

71
00:06:46.710 --> 00:06:48.180
Sanji!

72
00:06:49.270 --> 00:06:52.140
You guys can stand down as well.

73
00:06:53.490 --> 00:06:56.100
You have a rebellion
to stop, right, Vivi?

74
00:06:59.510 --> 00:07:02.780
I'll take care of him.

75
00:07:07.190 --> 00:07:11.160
Are you that ridiculous
transforming man?

76
00:07:11.160 --> 00:07:15.670
Stay out of my way.
Who are you anyway?!

77
00:07:16.920 --> 00:07:17.710
Go on.

78
00:07:19.440 --> 00:07:20.670
Look after Karoo.

79
00:07:28.630 --> 00:07:30.600
She's getting away!

80
00:07:31.360 --> 00:07:34.180
Don't you make a clown out of me!

81
00:07:34.570 --> 00:07:37.140
Now you get to die!

82
00:07:37.680 --> 00:07:41.770
Why don't I start by having
you return our marksman's...

83
00:07:44.500 --> 00:07:46.190
prized goggles to me?

84
00:07:46.190 --> 00:07:47.530
What?

85
00:07:48.070 --> 00:07:50.860
I won't go down as easily as him.

86
00:07:50.860 --> 00:07:53.370
You're in league with Straw Hat?

87
00:07:53.370 --> 00:07:56.830
Well, then, are you
the fabled Mr. Prince?

88
00:07:57.260 --> 00:07:58.090
Nope.

89
00:07:59.620 --> 00:08:03.340
My name is Sanji.
I'm a first-class cook of the sea.

90
00:08:05.560 --> 00:08:09.220
A cook? I happen to be
a first-class okama myself.

91
00:08:09.980 --> 00:08:14.180
A cook shouldn't attempt
to take on an underworld outfit!

92
00:08:14.830 --> 00:08:17.290
That label applies to both of us.

93
00:08:17.290 --> 00:08:19.530
I'm a cook and a pirate.

94
00:08:21.020 --> 00:08:22.860
It's gonna be an eye for an eye, is it?

95
00:08:25.190 --> 00:08:28.950
You got it. If you try
and harm this country, that is.

96
00:08:28.960 --> 00:08:32.920
Southeast Gate, Alubarna

97
00:08:38.070 --> 00:08:39.340
Chopper!

98
00:08:40.640 --> 00:08:44.620
Hey, Chopper!
Wake up! Hey! Come on!

99
00:08:46.080 --> 00:08:48.960
Usopp... Thank goodness
you're all right...

100
00:08:48.960 --> 00:08:52.840
Don't be silly! Are you all right?

101
00:08:52.840 --> 00:08:54.130
I'll live.

102
00:08:54.130 --> 00:08:55.310
So...

103
00:08:56.140 --> 00:08:58.640
this is what's left in the wake
of the Mr. 4 duo, huh?

104
00:08:58.640 --> 00:09:00.010
And here, I came to help!

105
00:09:00.010 --> 00:09:04.220
What a shame, for I—the champion
of the seas, the world's mightiest hero,

106
00:09:04.220 --> 00:09:07.980
the great Captain Usopp—wanted to
show off my fighting prowess!

107
00:09:07.980 --> 00:09:10.650
They're still around here,
somewhere. Be careful.

108
00:09:10.650 --> 00:09:12.030
What?! Say that first!

109
00:09:21.200 --> 00:09:25.040
What in the world is that?!
Nobody's even there!

110
00:09:25.410 --> 00:09:27.170
They've gone underground.

111
00:09:27.170 --> 00:09:31.010
Miss Merry Christmas is a mole woman,
thanks to the Mole-Mole Fruit.

112
00:09:31.440 --> 00:09:32.900
A mole woman?

113
00:09:32.900 --> 00:09:37.430
The other is Mr. 4, who bats fourth
as a cleanup hitter. He works with his dog.

114
00:09:37.970 --> 00:09:41.690
Huh? That makes no sense at all.
What do you mean?

115
00:09:45.350 --> 00:09:46.230
Here it comes!

116
00:09:46.560 --> 00:09:47.650
Look out!

117
00:09:55.800 --> 00:10:01.830
Mr. 4 & Miss Merry Christmas
vs
Usopp & Chopper

118
00:10:08.930 --> 00:10:10.770
Are you okay, Usopp?

119
00:10:14.840 --> 00:10:17.760
That was close!
You saved me! Thanks.

120
00:10:17.760 --> 00:10:19.890
What exactly was that just now?

121
00:10:19.890 --> 00:10:23.980
Like I said, Mr. 4 is a cleanup hitter,

122
00:10:24.600 --> 00:10:26.230
and he works with his dog.

123
00:10:26.230 --> 00:10:29.530
Like I said, that makes no sense at all.

124
00:10:30.230 --> 00:10:32.150
Ah! It's him!

125
00:10:33.020 --> 00:10:34.110
His dog...?

126
00:10:37.780 --> 00:10:39.450
What is that?!

127
00:10:47.710 --> 00:10:48.620
O-Oh, no!

128
00:10:48.620 --> 00:10:50.050
Wh-What?!

129
00:10:52.130 --> 00:10:53.170
What?!

130
00:10:53.920 --> 00:10:54.910
Here it comes!

131
00:10:54.910 --> 00:10:56.260
Again?!

132
00:11:02.510 --> 00:11:05.730
Run as far as you can, Usopp!

133
00:11:13.690 --> 00:11:14.700
Usopp!

134
00:11:21.090 --> 00:11:22.750
Are you all right, Usopp?!

135
00:11:23.740 --> 00:11:26.420
Like I said, what exactly was that?

136
00:11:27.040 --> 00:11:31.420
They're time bombs. They explode
even if they don't strike anything.

137
00:11:31.420 --> 00:11:34.420
Those two calculate
and coordinate the detonations.

138
00:11:35.020 --> 00:11:38.070
The bombs won't go off
until their time is up,

139
00:11:38.070 --> 00:11:41.360
so I thought I could catch one
and throw it back at them.

140
00:11:41.360 --> 00:11:45.950
Turns out they each weigh as much as
a wrecking ball and aren't so easily caught.

141
00:11:45.950 --> 00:11:49.400
That he can hit it with
a bat at such a high speed...

142
00:11:49.640 --> 00:11:53.480
Mr. 4 must possess
extraordinary strength.

143
00:11:59.840 --> 00:12:01.410
Huh...?

144
00:12:01.700 --> 00:12:05.410
Lassoo!

145
00:12:05.820 --> 00:12:10.370
Just how many tons is
that bat that he swings around?

146
00:12:10.370 --> 00:12:13.340
Hey, Mr. 4! Mr. 4!
La...!

147
00:12:13.960 --> 00:12:16.710
You doggone bastard, you!
You basset, you!

148
00:12:16.710 --> 00:12:20.380
Why are you just standing around?!
Let them have it, already!

149
00:12:20.380 --> 00:12:24.230
Come on, and let them have it!
Get on with it, and let them have it!

150
00:12:24.230 --> 00:12:27.310
Come on! Get on! Go on!
Have at it, you... you...

151
00:12:27.680 --> 00:12:29.310
ba... you ba!

152
00:12:32.060 --> 00:12:33.560
There she is! The mole person!

153
00:12:33.560 --> 00:12:34.980
She's a mole!

154
00:12:34.980 --> 00:12:38.020
I haven't even
transformed yet, ba! You ba!

155
00:12:38.650 --> 00:12:40.990
Chopper, it's all up to you now.

156
00:12:40.990 --> 00:12:43.700
Bury my body at sea
when I'm gone, would you?

157
00:12:43.700 --> 00:12:47.000
You just got done saying you came
to help me, you dumb jerk!

158
00:12:47.570 --> 00:12:48.580
Now, look!

159
00:12:49.080 --> 00:12:51.510
What is that dog-looking
thing over there?!

160
00:12:51.510 --> 00:12:54.540
You expect me to fight
an alien being as bizarre as that?!

161
00:12:54.540 --> 00:12:57.540
I'm a human, get it?!

162
00:12:57.540 --> 00:12:59.040
I'm a human, too!

163
00:12:59.040 --> 00:13:01.050
You're a monster, dummy!

164
00:13:01.050 --> 00:13:03.260
What about that long nose of yours?!

165
00:13:04.190 --> 00:13:06.210
His name is Lassoo.

166
00:13:06.210 --> 00:13:09.690
He's a gun that ate
the Dog-Dog Fruit: Dachshund.

167
00:13:10.180 --> 00:13:11.020
A gun?!

168
00:13:11.390 --> 00:13:14.480
Are you saying
that a gun ate a devil fruit?

169
00:13:15.120 --> 00:13:17.030
It's a new technique in the Grand Line.

170
00:13:17.030 --> 00:13:19.490
Even objects are able
to eat devil fruits.

171
00:13:19.850 --> 00:13:23.620
Ha! That's preposterous! How could
he move if he was originally a gun?

172
00:13:23.620 --> 00:13:25.730
A devil fruit can't have
a will of its own!

173
00:13:25.730 --> 00:13:28.280
And how can a gun eat anything
in the first place?!

174
00:13:28.280 --> 00:13:29.780
Shut up!

175
00:13:29.780 --> 00:13:32.660
Knowing won't do you any good
if you're dead, right?!

176
00:13:32.660 --> 00:13:36.250
A thing can't help it if it moves,
you know, you ba! Ba! Ba!

177
00:13:36.540 --> 00:13:38.590
Isn't that right, Mr. 4?

178
00:13:41.610 --> 00:13:45.770
Listen up. You guys aren't leaving
this place with your lives.

179
00:13:45.770 --> 00:13:48.850
Not after you've entered our territory, that is.

180
00:13:49.140 --> 00:13:53.330
And wouldn't you know it,
our territory's name is Molehill Zone Four.

181
00:13:58.350 --> 00:14:01.650
Sh-She's turning into a mole person!

182
00:14:06.740 --> 00:14:08.040
Ah. A penguin?

183
00:14:08.040 --> 00:14:10.240
I'm a mole, I tell you! You ba!

184
00:14:15.240 --> 00:14:16.670
She went underground!

185
00:14:17.160 --> 00:14:19.340
All right, now's my chance!

186
00:14:18.770 --> 00:14:20.330
Wait!

187
00:14:19.340 --> 00:14:22.300
You can take it from here!

188
00:14:24.250 --> 00:14:25.210
Watch out!

189
00:14:27.270 --> 00:14:28.500
It missed!

190
00:14:28.500 --> 00:14:29.220
A curveball?!

191
00:14:32.890 --> 00:14:33.680
No!

192
00:14:33.680 --> 00:14:35.520
It's above you, Usopp!

193
00:14:36.950 --> 00:14:37.690
Fly ball!

194
00:14:38.150 --> 00:14:39.880
Ha! No big deal!

195
00:14:39.880 --> 00:14:43.650
Looks like their cleanup hitter
can't bat a thousand, huh?

196
00:14:44.300 --> 00:14:47.910
I can dodge this one
with my eyes closed!

197
00:14:48.610 --> 00:14:49.580
The spin!

198
00:14:51.520 --> 00:14:53.000
Look out behind you!

199
00:14:57.210 --> 00:15:01.710
If he was just any cleanup hitter,
he wouldn't be Mr. 4!

200
00:15:25.510 --> 00:15:26.610
They're over there?!

201
00:15:27.230 --> 00:15:29.070
When did you have time to escape?!

202
00:15:32.620 --> 00:15:36.370
That form...! I get it,
you're a zoan type, are you?

203
00:15:36.370 --> 00:15:40.180
I had a feeling you weren't
just a normal person.

204
00:15:40.790 --> 00:15:45.090
Usopp, you'll be finished
if you stop moving.

205
00:15:45.090 --> 00:15:49.800
I get it. You're saying that if we stop,
they'll fire dozens more at us, huh?

206
00:15:53.470 --> 00:15:54.600
Get ready!

207
00:16:06.230 --> 00:16:08.570
If I can just send you flying...!

208
00:16:10.320 --> 00:16:16.410
Hold on. If we don't have a batter,
the game won't be any fun, will it?

209
00:16:20.420 --> 00:16:21.170
Chopper!

210
00:16:26.540 --> 00:16:28.840
Thank goodness I can do that.

211
00:16:29.550 --> 00:16:30.840
Why, you dirty mole!

212
00:16:32.380 --> 00:16:33.470
You bastard!

213
00:16:37.720 --> 00:16:41.080
Damn. If they keep darting
through these mole holes,

214
00:16:41.080 --> 00:16:44.350
the time I have to use a rumble ball
will be over too quickly.

215
00:16:46.980 --> 00:16:47.840
Huh?

216
00:16:48.480 --> 00:16:49.200
Huh...?

217
00:16:50.070 --> 00:16:54.200
Just where did that guy
with the long nose disappear to?

218
00:16:55.850 --> 00:16:58.150
They're right. Usopp is gone!

219
00:16:58.150 --> 00:17:00.750
I should warn you guys!

220
00:17:02.910 --> 00:17:05.370
Where are you?! Where did you go?!

221
00:17:06.000 --> 00:17:07.180
He wouldn't...!

222
00:17:07.180 --> 00:17:07.890
Indeed!

223
00:17:07.890 --> 00:17:10.490
You toiled away on these
underground passages.

224
00:17:10.490 --> 00:17:11.840
But you're not the only ones...

225
00:17:12.090 --> 00:17:15.050
who can navigate them.

226
00:17:17.460 --> 00:17:18.890
Usopp...

227
00:17:18.890 --> 00:17:22.690
You bastard! You were
in one of the holes?!

228
00:17:23.170 --> 00:17:25.900
Pound!

229
00:17:37.030 --> 00:17:39.020
Mr. 4!

230
00:17:43.660 --> 00:17:46.580
A five...
A five-ton hammer?!

231
00:17:47.090 --> 00:17:50.240
Where does that kid
keep such strength?!

232
00:17:57.510 --> 00:17:58.470
Five tons...

233
00:17:59.510 --> 00:18:01.810
Wh-Who are you?

234
00:18:04.070 --> 00:18:05.770
Traveler of the world's oceans,

235
00:18:06.710 --> 00:18:09.210
crusher of notorious foes as I go,

236
00:18:09.210 --> 00:18:11.680
and sinker of countless ships.

237
00:18:11.680 --> 00:18:16.740
Out of fear, people call me
the King of Destruction.

238
00:18:17.740 --> 00:18:20.700
Remember my name well.

239
00:18:21.620 --> 00:18:25.700
Captain Usopp!

240
00:18:25.700 --> 00:18:28.300
Awesome! Awesome! Awesome!

241
00:18:28.300 --> 00:18:30.550
That was awesome, Usopp!

242
00:18:28.790 --> 00:18:31.170
Yeah, thank you, thank you, baby!

243
00:18:30.550 --> 00:18:32.250
Awesome! Awesome!

244
00:18:31.170 --> 00:18:33.720
Thank you. I'm signing
autographs later.

245
00:18:32.250 --> 00:18:35.920
I-I've underestimated
your ability up until now!

246
00:18:35.400 --> 00:18:36.320
Hey!

247
00:18:38.130 --> 00:18:40.060
Mr. 4 is...

248
00:18:41.460 --> 00:18:45.910
He's not moving.
C-Could I have hit him that hard?

249
00:18:45.910 --> 00:18:49.860
No, hold on. Either way,
this is my chance, right?

250
00:18:50.290 --> 00:18:52.190
You, too, penguin!

251
00:18:52.190 --> 00:18:55.160
Take this five-ton hammer!

252
00:18:56.870 --> 00:18:59.790
Usopp Pound!

253
00:19:01.200 --> 00:19:04.030
She escaped!
Where are you, penguin?!

254
00:19:04.030 --> 00:19:06.540
I told you, I'm a mole, you ba!

255
00:19:06.540 --> 00:19:07.950
